## Top 20 improvement ideas (re-ranked after answers)

 1. Word export fidelity (Word is THE deliverable — confirmed by James).
    [DONE v2.044]: HTML-escaping of all user text in Word/Excel/Print exports;
    Word running header + footer with Page X of Y fields.
    REMAINING: open the .doc in real desktop Word and review pagination/table
    widths; consider a true .docx (e.g. via api/report.py docx path) so the
    file isn't flagged as HTML-based; table of contents; embed crime map
    snapshot images in export.
 2. [DONE v2.043] Multi-assessment manager — toolbar "Assessments" button;
    per-assessment localStorage keys + index; open/create/delete/switch with
    auto-save before switching; legacy single-slot data migrated on load.
    Possible follow-ups: rename-in-list, search/filter for long lists.
 3. [DONE v2.052] Undo/redo (Ctrl+Z) — debounced history stack covers the
    working-assessment fields (context, assets, threats, all scoring grids,
    meetings, POIs, treatments, threat/treatment DB, SBD compliance). Ctrl+Z
    undoes, Ctrl+Y/Ctrl+Shift+Z redoes; toolbar buttons mirror availability.
    Skipped while focus is in a text field so native field-undo still works.
 4. [DONE v2.049] Interactive dashboard matrix — Dashboard risk-count cards
    click through to a filtered Risk Register (severity banner + clear filter).
 5. Reviewer workflow — per-risk comments with author/timestamp, and a
    review/sign-off status per section (draft → reviewed → issued).
 6. Assessment compare/diff — load two saved JSON files and show risk deltas
    (pre/post design change, year-on-year review).
 7. Treatment prioritisation — capture indicative cost + effort per measure,
    auto-build a quick-win / planned / long-term roadmap table for the report.
 8. Executive summary auto-draft — generate narrative text from the data (top
    risks, crime trend, posture) as a starting point for the assessor.
 9. [DONE v2.048] QA / completeness gate before export — Word/Excel export
    runs a checklist (unscored threats, missing ALARP justifications, empty
    required context fields) and confirms before exporting anyway.
10. Photo attachments on POIs and Existing Controls (site walkaround
    evidence), included in Word/PDF export.
11. Tablet/mobile site-survey mode — POI capture optimised for touch on a
    walkaround; the desktop layout is dense on small screens.
12. Offline crime-data snapshot — store fetched Police.uk data inside the
    saved assessment so reports are reproducible later (data changes monthly).
13. Non-UK mode — Police.uk only covers England/Wales/NI; allow manual crime
    stats entry + international threat-level sources for overseas sites.
14. Proper accounts/backend — replace APP_PASSWORD + GitHub-token-in-browser
    with real auth and server-side persistence (also fixes: plaintext password
    in session cookie, secret baked into client bundle by build.js).
15. Org template library — save/share company-standard criteria text, threat
    sets and treatment libraries as versioned template files.
16. [DONE v2.047] Full WCAG AA pass — modal focus traps + restore-on-close,
    role=dialog/aria-modal on the Setup Wizard, aria-live toasts, score
    buttons as role=radio/radiogroup with aria-label/aria-checked.
17. [DONE v2.050] Keyboard bulk scoring — Shift+1-5 applies to the whole row,
    Alt+1-5 applies to the whole column, Ctrl/Cmd+D copies the cell above down.
18. Performance: split the 616KB single file (lazy-load Leaflet, html2canvas,
    crime tab) for faster first paint; consider build step producing chunks.
19. [DONE v2.053, partial] Automated tests + CI — Playwright smoke test
    (loads the app, walks every sidebar tab checking for console/page errors,
    adds an asset) plus a GitHub Action running it on every PR and push to
    main (`tests/`, `playwright.config.js`, `.github/workflows/smoke-tests.yml`).
    REMAINING: per-export-function tests (Word/Excel/print HTML structure),
    coverage of the scoring grids/treatments/SBD tabs beyond "did it render",
    and a visual-regression pass.
20. [DONE v2.051] In-app help/onboarding — "?" tooltips next to TA, DBT,
    ALARP, Likelihood and Capability/Intent linking through to Methodology.

