## Known security items (deliberately not changed without sign-off)
- middleware.js stores the plaintext APP_PASSWORD in the session cookie —
  switch to a hashed/opaque token (needs matching change in api/db.js +
  api/report.py).
- build.js bakes APP_PASSWORD into the obfuscated client JS via
  __API_SECRET__ — recoverable by anyone with the file; rely on the session
  cookie instead.
- projects/ (client assessment data) is committed to git history — confirm
  this is intended; consider a private data repo.

## Done this session (v2.039–v2.040)
- Crime comparison month-maths bug (Jan/Feb invalid months); 3-month fallback
- Duplicate Assessment no longer wipes autosave (data-loss window)
- Load-file validation (shape checks) + FileReader error handler
- Escape + ARIA roles on confirm dialog and back-up browser modal
- Keyboard focus outlines on all button variants; meta description/theme-color
- Residual Risk table header overlap fix; button label nowrap; POI empty-state
  CTA; standardised "Copy to Word"
